body:
Looks like with 0.1.20 it works fine
```sh
python3 -m pip install https://storage.googleapis.com/ml-pipeline/release/0.1.20/kfp.tar.gz --upgrade
```

Next question is that
```
/usr/local/bin/dsl-compile --py deployer.py --output deployer.tar.gz
```
does not produce any useful logs but documentation has no further steps

@dtrawins, @mzegla, Hi! May I ask you to point which steps should go after `dsl-compile` at [example_kubeflow_pipelines/ovms_deployer](https://github.com/IntelAI/OpenVINO-model-server/tree/master/example_kubeflow_pipelines/ovms_deployer) and [example_kubeflow_pipelines/openvino](https://github.com/IntelAI/OpenVINO-model-server/tree/master/example_kubeflow_pipelines/openvino) guides? And what's the difference between them?

@dkurt  Once you genereate deployer.tar.gz file, you can import it in KubeFlow Pipeline GUI interface. When the pipeline is imported you are create an experiment, which should work with the default parameters.

Do you know the best way to deploy Kubeflow pipelines locally? Based on my experience, it's not straightforward: https://github.com/kubeflow/website/pull/1609, https://github.com/canonical-labs/kubeflow-tools/issues/15

There are three ways to Getting Started with KF: https://www.kubeflow.org/docs/started/workstation/getting-started-linux/ but neither of them works for me.
So far I was testing kubeflow pipelines in GCP. I can ask my colleagues, tough. If they can share some tips, I'll send it via email.

@dtrawins, Thanks!

I could run Kubeflow locally with https://github.com/kubeflow/website/blob/master/content/docs/other-guides/virtual-dev/getting-started-multipass.md#install-kubeflow-using-microk8s. Have not tried OVMS with it yet.
